The third step is to construct the Markov transfer field M (Equation 3), which achieves the purpose of representing the spatial distribution of transfer probabilities by arranging each transfer probability in the Markov transfer matrix W along the time order. Finally, the matrix elements are mapped to 2D matrix pixel values, and the transformed 2D image is obtained by displaying the transfer probabilities between different states and visualizing the transfer patterns and correlations in the data (

